<strong>The following tests require a music playlist consisting of 2 or more pieces of music.</strong>

<strong>Multimedia keys (Totem)</strong>
Case ID: khk-001
This tests that totem can respond to Multimedia keys on a keyboard
<dl>
    <dt>Click on Ubuntu Logo, search for any open Movie Player</dt> 
        <dd>Movie player should open</dd>
    <dt>Open a playlist</dt>
    <dt>Press on the Play key (This can be combined with Pause key)</dt> 
        <dd>This should start playing the playlist</dd> 
    <dt>Press on the Stop key. To stop the track playing</dt> 
        <dd>The Pause (or Play key if there is no separate Pause key) should pauses playback</dd> 
    <dt>Press on the Play key. To start the track playing again</dt> wing only apply if you have the internet hot keys.
        <dd>Playing should resume</dd> 
    <dt>Press on the Volume Up key</dt>
        <dd>The volume should increase</dd>  
    <dt>Press on the Volume Down Key</dt> 
        <dd>The volume should decrease</dd> 
    <dt>Press on the Volume Mute key</dt> 
        <dd>The volume should mute</dd> 
    <dt>Press on the Volume Mute key again</dt> 
        <dd>This should unmute the audio</dd> 
    <dt>Press on the Forward Track key</dt>
        <dd>Totem skips forward a track</dd> 
    <dt>Press on the Reverse Track key</dt> 
        <dd>Totem skips backward a track</dd> 
</dl>

<strong>Multimedia keys (Rhythmbox or Banshee)</strong>
Case ID: khk-002

<dl>
    <dt>Click on Ubuntu Logo, search for and open Music Player</dt>
        <dd>Either Banshee or Rhythmbox should open</dd>
    <Open a playlist</dt>
    <dt>Press on the Play key (This can be combined with Pause key)</dt>
        <dd>The playlist should start to play</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Stop key</dt>
        <dd>The track should stop playing</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Play key</dt>
        <dd>The track should start playing again</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Volume Up key</dt>
        <dd>The volume should increase</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Volume Down Key</dt>
        <dd>The volume should decrease</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Volume Mute key</dt>
        <dd>The volume should mute</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Volume Mute key</dt>
        <dd>The volume should unmute</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Forward Track key</dt>
        <dd>The next track should start playing</dd>
    <dt>Press on the Reverse Track key</dt> 
        <dd>The previous track should start playing</dd>
</dl>

<strong>Email (Thunderbird or Evolution)</strong>
Case ID: khk-003
The following only apply if you have the internet hot keys.
<dl>
    <dt>Press on the E-mail key</dt>
        <dd>Your default email app should open</dd>
</dl>


<strong>Internet (firefox)</strong>
Case ID: khk-004
The following only apply if you have the internet hot keys.
<dl>
    <dt>Press on the Home or WWW key</dt>
        <dd>The default internet browser should open</dd>
    <dt>Go to www.ubuntu.com</dt> 
    <dt>Go to planet.ubuntu.com</dt> 
    <dt>Press the Back key</dt>
        <dd>The ubuntu home page should open</dd>
    <dt>Press the Forward key</dt> 
        <dd>The planet ubuntu page should open</dd>
    <dt>Open a webpage. Press the Stop key before the page has fully loaded</dt> 
        <dd>The page should stop loading</dd>        
    <dt>Press the Home key</dt> 
        <dd>Your homepage should open</dd>
    <dt>Press the Favorites key</dt> 
        <dd>The bookmarks sidebar should open</dd>
</dl>


<strong>Search (tracker)</strong>
Case ID: khk-005
<dl>
    <dt>Press the Search key</dt>
    <dt>The tracker desktop search tool should open</dt> 
</dl>

